#:: Version:      1.07
#::
#:: Purpose:      Configure this Linux host as a VPN-backed router that forwards LAN
#::               traffic through a supported VPN CLI and fails closed if the VPN drops.
#::
#:: Value:        Useful when a Linux host or VM should act as the default gateway for
#::               client devices while keeping their internet traffic behind NordVPN,
#::               Mullvad, or Proton VPN.
#::
#:: Usage:        Run with sudo on the machine that should provide VPN-backed routing.
#::               The script connects the VPN, applies forwarding/NAT firewall rules,
#::               then opens a terminal monitor.
#::
#:: Examples:
#::               sudo rtd-start-vpn-router
#::
